    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-102">A<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>只能的子項目<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-102">A <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> can only be a child element of a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-103">此外，<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>只能是第一個子系，最後一個子系或這兩個的第一個和最後一個子項目<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-103">Additionally, a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> can only be the first child, last child, or both the first and last child elements in a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-104">位置<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>中的項目<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>表示，如果本文包含在其他片段中，如果其他片段之前，或依照目前的片段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-104">The location of the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> element in a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> indicates if the story is contained in additional fragments, and if the additional fragments either precede or follow the current fragment.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-105">A<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>中的第一個項目為<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>指出劇本的開始。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-105">A <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> as the first element in a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> indicates the start of a story.</span></span>  
  
```  
<!-- Fragment 1 -->  
<StoryFragment>  
  <StoryBreak />   <!-- Identifies the start of a story when          -->  
                   <!-- immediately after an opening <StoryFragment>. -->  
  <ParagraphStructure>  
    <NamedElement NameReference="a" />  
    <NamedElement NameReference="b" />  
  </ParagraphStructure>  
</StoryFragment>   <!-- Story continues in the next <StoryFragment>.  -->  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-106">A<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>中的最後一個項目為<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>表示本文的結尾。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-106">A <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> as the last element in a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> indicates the end of a story.</span></span>  
  
```  
<!-- Fragment 2 -->  
<StoryFragment>    <!-- Story continued from prior <StoryFragment>.    -->  
  <ParagraphStructure>    
    <NamedElement NameReference="c" />  
  </ParagraphStructure>  
  <StoryBreak />   <!-- Identifies the end of a story when             -->  
                   <!-- immediately before a closing </StoryFragment>. -->  
</StoryFragment>  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-107">本文包含在單一<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>有兩個<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>為片段的第一個和最後一個子元素的項目。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-107">A story that is contained in a single <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> will have two <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> elements as the first and last child elements of the fragment.</span></span>  
  
```  
<!-- Fragments 1 and 2 Merged -->  
<ParagraphStructure>  
  <NamedElement NameReference="a" />  
  <NamedElement NameReference="b" />  
  <NamedElement NameReference="c" />  
</ParagraphStructure>  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-108"><xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> 項目完全包含在單一頁面會以開頭和結尾<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>後的內容會完全包含在單一片段中的項目。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-108"><xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> elements that are entirely contained on one page will start and end with <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> elements since the content is completely contained in a single fragment.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-109">位置<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>中的項目<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>時，您想要存取文件中的正向或反向方向中的內容。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-109">The position of <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> elements in a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> is useful when you want to access content in either forward or reverse direction in the document.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-110">例如當合併片段正向順序<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>，結尾<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>表示結束劇本及確認有沒有更多的片段，以合併。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-110">For example when merging fragments in forward order, a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> that ends with a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> indicates the end of the story and that there are no more fragments to merge.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-111">同樣地當合併劇本片段反向順序<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>開頭<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>指出該劇本有開頭是沒有先前的片段，以合併。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-111">Similarly when merging story fragments in reverse order, a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> that starts with a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> indicates the start of the story and that there are no prior fragments to merge.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-112">處理劇本片段正向或反向方向的能力是很重要的許多應用程式使用。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-112">The ability to process story fragments in either forward or reverse directions is important for many application uses.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-113">例如，跨越分頁符號的段落分成多個劇本片段，每個頁面一個片段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-113">For example, a paragraph that spans page breaks is divided into multiple story fragments, one fragment for each page.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-114">提供按三下功能，以選取並複製到剪貼簿的整個段落的使用者介面必須能段落跨越多個頁面時，合併多個劇本片段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-114">A user interface that provides a triple-click feature to select and copy a whole paragraph to the clipboard must be able to merge multiple story fragments when a paragraph spans multiple pages.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-115">此外使用者 triple-按一下組件的段落開頭的第一頁上，如果應用程式必須識別，<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>開頭<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>但未以結尾<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-115">Additionally if the user triple-clicks on part of a paragraph that starts on the first page, the application must identify that the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> starts with a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> but does not end with a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-116">這表示，<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>包含在下一個頁面必須載入並加入至目前的片段結尾。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-116">This would indicate that the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> that is contained on the next page must be loaded and added to the end of the current fragment.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-117">同樣的使用者 triple-按一下段落最後一頁上的部分，如果應用程式必須識別，<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>結尾<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>但不是以開頭<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-117">Similarly if the user triple-clicks on part of the paragraph located on the last page, the application must identify that the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> ends with a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> but does not begin with a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-118">這表示，<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>也就是包含在先前的頁面必須載入並加入至目前片段開頭。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-118">This would indicate that the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> that is contained on previous page must be loaded and added to the start of the current fragment.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-119">應用程式也應該能夠處理大型段落跨越三個或多個頁面的大小寫的正向與反向說明，且使用者的選取範圍點的位置是內部的頁面。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-119">The application should also be able to process both forward and reverse directions for the case of large paragraphs that span three or more pages and where the user's selection point is on an inner page.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7afa3-120">因為<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>僅限於單一頁面上，使用<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak>項目可讓每個<xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment>包含格式正確的 XML，但仍有跨整份文件的階層式結構。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7afa3-120">Since a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> is limited to a single page, the use of <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryBreak> elements allow each <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.StoryFragment> to contain well-formed XML but still have a hierarchical structure across an entire document.</span></span>  
  
 ]]></format>
